Seems a little light on answers
Beast Within solves a lot of problems
Also super heavy on enchantments without any way to recur them (outside of EWit) and most are 'do nothing's when they come into play.

like the actual number?
I'm with <@U4V5EHQ2G> on Beast Within...also potentially some exile answers to deal with indestructible, and I don't see any card draw of any note.
[[Path of Discovery]] would fit here, but you need some kind of draw.

I had to change the default grouping and then it appeared
Ah... Still weird
Still...3.5 seems on the high side for a deck like this.
But also, what're your goals?
We're just looking at it in isolation.
yeah
this is more of a casual deck
not trying to go overboard like several of my others
but the goal is to just wittle people down with slimefoots ability and grind out tribal token value
i do agree on the enchantments though
running toomany
A few are fine but you should replace several with card draw and answers. Also not enough sac outlets.
<@U3L7A68JC> which enchantments do you suggest cutting? I can't decide which are less important
they all grind out so much value
or are wincons

Yet they're also 'do nothings' for the most part...you cast them and nothing happens for a turn or so. You won't survive long enough to grind that value because the deck doesn't seems set up to slow your opponents down.
ok

You have too many enchantments that only gain value from exiling stuff from a gy, and that might not happen until later game, if at all. Snake Umbra is a no-no to me, the chances are ayou won't be doing as much combat damage as you think since most of your saprolings are tiny.
The CMC is pretty high overall. I don't like any of the auras
[[Death Mutation]] doesn't seem worth 8...you're killing a single thing.
